WEBVTT

00:00.375 --> 00:01.976
<i>Previously on "The Arrangement"...</i>

00:02.001 --> 00:03.033
"Kill Plan."

00:03.058 --> 00:04.223
Let's talk about this movie.

00:04.375 --> 00:05.862
This... this is new territory.

00:05.862 --> 00:07.476
You've never had a film lose money before.

00:07.561 --> 00:08.727
We should prepare.

00:08.795 --> 00:10.462
Maybe go back to morning sessions.

00:10.530 --> 00:11.629
So where do you fit in?

00:11.698 --> 00:12.964
We're gonna make you an icon.

00:13.280 --> 00:14.846
<i>Your mom was a wonderful woman.</i>

00:15.334 --> 00:16.663
<i>She meant a lot to me.</i>

00:16.663 --> 00:18.229
If you need anything, please...

00:18.298 --> 00:19.677
My door's always open.

00:20.707 --> 00:22.106
Oh, whoa, Wes. Whoa.

00:22.175 --> 00:23.441
That's not where I was going with this.

00:23.509 --> 00:24.942
We'd be great parents.

00:25.011 --> 00:27.044
Structured, focused, affectionate.

00:27.113 --> 00:30.381
<i>Please welcome
the incredible Xavier Hughes.</i>

00:30.450 --> 00:32.316
That's my boyfriend.

00:32.384 --> 00:33.928
Have you ever acted before?

00:34.821 --> 00:36.454
He has something undeniable, though.

00:36.522 --> 00:38.478
<i>A whole lot of buzz right now.</i>

00:39.292 --> 00:40.591
I thought you were on my side.

00:40.660 --> 00:42.360
I think I need to take a step back.

00:42.428 --> 00:44.662
You're looking for dirt on IHM, yeah?

00:44.731 --> 00:47.105
Man, I've got stories that
will make your blood run cold.

00:47.533 --> 00:49.819
I have no idea what you're talking about.

00:50.737 --> 00:52.436
What's up, guys? I'm Erin Lim.

00:52.505 --> 00:54.372
And you're watching "The Rundown."

00:54.440 --> 00:56.040
<i>We all know Kyle West kills
it in the looks department.</i>

00:56.109 --> 00:57.608
But for the first time in his career,

00:57.677 --> 00:59.310
he's got a flop on his hands.

00:59.379 --> 01:01.145
<i>His movie "The Kill Plan" is so</i>

01:01.214 --> 01:02.871
not killing it at the box office.

01:02.896 --> 01:04.036
Let's break it down.

01:04.061 --> 01:06.061
<i>For starters, after
demanding final approval</i>

01:06.086 --> 01:07.551
on basically everything,

01:07.551 --> 01:10.091
<i>Kyle cast his real life
and real unknown girlfriend</i>

01:10.116 --> 01:11.099
<i>Megan Morrison.</i>

01:11.099 --> 01:13.122
<i>Then he had to recast
her with Amelia Briggs.</i>

01:13.147 --> 01:14.913
Because, uh, nudes.

01:14.982 --> 01:16.682
Sounds like trouble in Kyanastan.

01:16.750 --> 01:20.519
Oh, and the little issue of
going 45 million over budget.

01:20.587 --> 01:22.254
80 million. 125 million.

01:22.323 --> 01:24.089
Whatever. It's only money.

01:24.158 --> 01:26.397
Except that "Kill Plan"
only made 11 million

01:26.397 --> 01:27.915
<i>in its opening weekend.</i>

01:27.915 --> 01:30.453
<i>I hate math as much as anyone,
but that's problematic.</i>

01:30.478 --> 01:33.246
<i>And then the critics started
throwing some serious shade.</i>

01:33.315 --> 01:34.747
<i>"Unwatchable." "Mind-numbing."</i>

01:34.816 --> 01:37.798
<i>"So bad." Ow, man. That hurt.</i>

01:37.975 --> 01:39.275
<i>I guess this is what you get</i>

01:39.343 --> 01:40.784
<i>when you demand creative control.</i>

01:40.809 --> 01:41.948
<i>So, Kyle, what have we learned?</i>

01:41.948 --> 01:43.615
<i>First of all, stay beautiful always.</i>

01:43.683 --> 01:45.283
<i>And next time, maybe
stay in your lane, too?</i>

01:45.352 --> 01:46.918
<i>Oh, but wait... You're
directing a movie...</i>

01:46.987 --> 01:49.265
It's like a train wreck.
You can't look away.

01:49.482 --> 01:52.875
Oh, it's just information.
Helps me plan for the future.

01:58.299 --> 01:59.699
Can we pretend it never happened?

01:59.768 --> 02:01.004
Just for a few hours.

02:01.636 --> 02:03.069
I want to make tonight perfect.

02:09.744 --> 02:11.210
This is too good.

02:13.681 --> 02:15.204
Be careful of my dress.

02:16.751 --> 02:20.820
<i>♪
Reckless souls ♪</i>

02:25.326 --> 02:27.160
Kyle, how do you bounce back

02:27.228 --> 02:29.061
from a failure like the "Kill
Plan"? What's your next role?

02:29.130 --> 02:30.963
I honestly haven't given
much thought to acting.

02:31.032 --> 02:33.172
I'm just keeping my focus on
directing this amazing actress.

02:33.601 --> 02:35.234
- Kyle, Megan, look over here!
- Kyle!

02:35.259 --> 02:37.786
Oh-ho, there's a fan poll on Dark Horizons

02:37.829 --> 02:39.662
for who should be the next Agent Jane.

02:39.731 --> 02:41.297
I'm number three.

02:41.366 --> 02:43.310
How do they know I'm even up for the part?

02:43.389 --> 02:45.389
Creative Partners, earning their 10%.

02:45.458 --> 02:48.026
I am a huge Agent Jane fan.

02:48.260 --> 02:50.336
You make the perfect avenging angel.

02:51.230 --> 02:53.022
- They're in the back.
- Thanks, Zach.

02:57.303 --> 03:00.006
- What's he doing here?
- A little coordination.

